.TH TR_ABORT_IND 7 "$Date: 2004/10/25 09:16:18 $" "$Name:  $" "Transaction Interface (TRI)"
.SH NAME
.PP
.B TR_ABORT_IND
\- Abort Indication
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
This message consists of a
.BR M_PROTO (9)
message block formatted as follows:
.sp
.nf
\fC\s-1\
typedef struct TR_abort_req {
    ulong PRIM_type;          /* Always TR_ABORT_REQ */
    ulong TRANS_id;           /* Transaction id */
    ulong ABORT_cause;        /* Cause of the abort */
    ulong OPT_length;         /* Options structure length */
    ulong OPT_offset;         /* Options structure offset */
} TR_abort_req_t;
\fR\s+1
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This primitive indicates to the user that either a request for association has been denied or an
existing association has been aborted.
The format of this message is one
.BR M_PROTO (9)
message block possibly followed by one or more
.BR M_DATA (9)
message blocks if there is any user data associated with the primitive.
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
.PP
The fields of this message have the following meanings:
.TP 16
.I PRIM_type
identifies the primitive type.
Always
.BR TR_ABORT_REQ .
.TP
.I TRANS_id
is the transaction identifier that identifies which association was aborted.
.TP
.I ABORT_cause
is the cause of the abort.
The cause codes are protocol specific.
.TP
.I OPT_length
is the length of the protocol options associated with the abort.
.TP
.I OPT_offset
is the offset from the beginning of the
.BR M_PROTO (9)
message block where the protocol options start.
.SH MODES
.PP
Only connection-mode.
.SH ORIGINATOR
.PP
Transaction provider.
